  "doc_id": "8480",
  "text": "Each trial of the grasp-use conflict task began with the presentation of a 400-by-400 pixel color photograph of a tool on a computer monitor. Participants were asked to \"show how you would use the tool as if you were holding and using it\" with the left hand. Four practice trials with feedback (using items different than in the task itself) were given at the start of the task. As per [CITATION_1] , if a participant gestured the action as if their hand was the tool (body-part-asobject error), they were reminded to \"show how you would use the tool as if you were actually holding it in your hand\". The first of these errors was corrected and the participant was permitted a second try.",
